@startuml
title Diagramme de sequence - Flux de demarrage du serveur

actor "Node.js Runtime" as Runtime
participant "server.js" as Server
participant "app.js\ncreateApp()" as AppFactory
participant "Express App" as ExpressApp
participant "HTTP Server" as HttpServer
participant "socket.js" as SocketLayer
participant "Socket.IO" as SocketIO
database "MongoDB Atlas" as MongoDB
participant "userMaintenance" as Maintenance

Runtime -> Server: Executer le backend
Server -> Server: Charger .env
Server -> AppFactory: createApp()
AppFactory -> ExpressApp: Initialiser Express
AppFactory -> ExpressApp: Configurer middlewares
AppFactory -> ExpressApp: Monter les routes API
AppFactory -> ExpressApp: Ajouter notFound + errorHandler
AppFactory --> Server: app

Server -> HttpServer: http.createServer(app)
Server -> SocketLayer: initializeSocket(server)
SocketLayer -> SocketIO: Initialiser Socket.IO
SocketLayer --> Server: io
Server -> ExpressApp: app.set('io', io)

Server -> Server: connectDB()
Server -> MongoDB: mongoose.connect(MONGODB_URI)

alt Connexion MongoDB reussie
  MongoDB --> Server: Connexion OK
  Server -> Maintenance: backfillEmailVerificationIfDisabled()
  Maintenance --> Server: Resultat de synchronisation
  Server -> MongoDB: Enregistrer les listeners\nerror/disconnected/reconnected
else Echec de connexion
  MongoDB --> Server: Erreur de connexion
  Server -> Server: setTimeout(connectDB, 5000)
end

Server -> Server: Enregistrer SIGTERM et SIGINT
Server -> HttpServer: server.listen(PORT)
HttpServer --> Server: Serveur en ecoute
Server -> Server: Logger le port de demarrage

@enduml
